attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, if the Defending Pokémon tries to attack, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack doesn't happen.

cards.name: Quaxwell
cards.text: These Pokémon constantly run through shallow waters to train their legs, then compete with each other to see which of them kicks most gracefully.

cards.name: Frigibax
cards.text: Frigibax absorbs heat through its dorsal fin and converts the heat into ice energy. The higher the temperature, the more energy Frigibax stores.

cards.name: Arctibax
cards.text: Arctibax freezes the air around it, protecting its face with an ice mask and turning its dorsal fin into a blade of ice.

cards.name: Baxcalibur

abilities.name: Super Cold
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn, you may attach a Basic Water Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon.

cards.text: This Pokémon blasts cryogenic air out from its mouth. This air can instantly freeze even liquid-hot lava.

cards.name: Raichu
cards.text: Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.

attacks.name: Electrocharge
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Lightning Energy cards and attach them to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Thunderbolt
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

cards.name: Mismagius

abilities.name: Magical Flick
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may move an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon to 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

cards.text: Its cry sounds like an incantation. It is said the cry may rarely be imbued with happiness-giving power.

cards.name: Gothorita
cards.text: This Pokémon will hypnotize children to put them to sleep before carrying them away. Be wary of nights when the starlight is bright.

attacks.name: Mind Bend
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

cards.name: Sandygast
cards.text: If it loses its shovel, it will stick something else— like a branch—in its head to make do until it finds another shovel.

cards.name: Rabsca
cards.text: The body that supports the ball barely moves. Therefore, it is thought that the true body of this Pokémon is actually inside the ball.

attacks.name: Revival Blessing
attacks.text: Put a Pokémon from your discard pile onto your Bench.

attacks.name: Psybeam
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

cards.name: Tinkatink
cards.text: It swings its handmade hammer around to protect itself, but the hammer is often stolen by Pokémon that eat metal.

attacks.name: Scrap Pickup
attacks.text: Put an Item card from your discard pile into your hand.

cards.name: Tinkatuff
cards.text: This Pokémon will attack groups of Pawniard and Bisharp, gathering metal from them in order to create a large and sturdy hammer.

attacks.name: Play Rough
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

attacks.name: Pulverizing Press
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

cards.name: Paldean Tauros
cards.text: This kind of Tauros, known as the Combat Breed, is distinguished by its thick, powerful muscles and its fierce disposition.

attacks.name: Raging Horns
attacks.text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Combat Tackle
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

cards.name: Sudowoodo
cards.text: Although it always pretends to be a tree, its composition appears more similar to rock than to vegetation.

attacks.name: Hit and Hide
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

cards.name: Nacli
cards.text: It was born in a layer of rock salt deep under the earth. This species was particularly treasured in the old days, as they would share precious salt.

attacks.name: Salt Coating
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

cards.name: Paldean Wooper
cards.text: After losing a territorial struggle, Wooper began living on land. The Pokémon changed over time, developing a poisonous film to protect its body.

attacks.name: Find a Home
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Stadium card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

cards.name: Tyranitar
cards.text: Extremely strong, it can change the landscape. It is so insolent that it doesn't care about others.

attacks.name: Rout

attacks.name: Dread Mountain

cards.text: The color of the poisonous saliva depends on what the Pokémon eats. Grafaiai covers its fingers in its saliva and draws patterns on trees in forests.

attacks.name: Spit Poison

attacks.name: Shoot Through

attacks.name: Send Back
